---
import LegalPage from "../layouts/legal-page.astro";
---

<LegalPage
  title="Privacy Policy — Reporili"
  description="How Reporili handles ZIP uploads, GitHub repository URLs, server logs, Google Gemini processing, and browser localStorage."
  documentTitle="Privacy Policy"
>
  <p>
    Reporili (“we”, “us”, “our”) operates an online tool at
    <a href="https://reporili.tech">https://reporili.tech</a> that analyzes source code you
    provide (via ZIP upload or GitHub repository URL) and generates draft legal documents using
    automated analysis and artificial intelligence.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Scope</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use Reporili. It applies to
    visitors and users of the public website and document-generation service. We do not offer user
    accounts or registration at this time.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Information we process</h2>
  <h3>2.1 Content you submit</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>ZIP archives</strong> you upload (may contain source code, configuration, comments,
      and other project files).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>GitHub repository URLs</strong> you submit. If the repository is public, or
      accessible with credentials configured on our server, we download a snapshot archive via the
      GitHub API for analysis. We do not use GitHub OAuth or ask you to sign in to GitHub through
      Reporili.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You are responsible for ensuring you have the right to submit this content (see our
    <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>).
  </p>

  <h3>2.2 Derived analysis data</h3>
  <p>
    To generate documents, we scan submitted content in memory and produce a technical summary
    (for example: detected frameworks, integrations, file paths, and pattern categories such as
    authentication or payments). This summary is sent to our AI provider (see Section 4).
  </p>

  <h3>2.3 Technical and log data</h3>
  <p>When you use the service, our infrastructure may automatically record:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>IP address</li>
    <li>Date and time of request</li>
    <li>Browser type and User-Agent</li>
    <li>Request metadata (for example, URLs accessed, HTTP status)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These are collected for security, abuse prevention, rate limiting, and troubleshooting.
  </p>

  <h3>2.4 Optional browser storage (your device)</h3>
  <p>
    If you enable “Save generations”, prior results may be stored in your browser’s
    <strong>localStorage</strong> on your device only. We do not receive or store this history on
    our servers.
  </p>

  <h2>3. What we do not collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not require account registration, passwords, or profile information.</li>
    <li>We do not operate a user database for Reporili at this time.</li>
    <li>
      We do not use third-party advertising or analytics trackers on the website (as of the date
      above).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. How we use information</h2>
  <p>We use submitted content and derived summaries solely to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Analyze your project and detect relevant technical patterns;</li>
    <li>Generate draft Privacy Policy, Terms of Service, and Disclaimer text;</li>
    <li>Operate, secure, and improve the service;</li>
    <li>Prevent abuse (including zip bombs, excessive requests, and malicious uploads).</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Where the GDPR or similar laws apply, we rely on performance of the service you request,
    legitimate interests in security and abuse prevention, and compliance with law.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Subprocessors and international transfers</h2>
  <h3>5.1 Google (Gemini API)</h3>
  <p>
    We use <strong>Google’s Generative AI API (Gemini)</strong> to produce draft document text. A
    <strong>technical summary derived from your submitted code</strong> (not your full repository)
    is transmitted to Google for processing.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Google privacy policy:
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
        >https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      Google Cloud terms (as applicable):
      <a href="https://cloud.google.com/terms" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
        >https://cloud.google.com/terms</a>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Google may process data in the United States and other countries. By using Reporili, you
    acknowledge this transfer.
  </p>

  <h3>5.2 GitHub</h3>
  <p>
    If you provide a GitHub URL, we request repository archives from <strong>GitHub, Inc.</strong>
    subject to GitHub’s terms and privacy policy:
    <a
      href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      target="_blank"
      >GitHub Privacy Statement</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h3>5.3 Hosting</h3>
  <p>
    The service runs on infrastructure we control. Server logs may be retained for a limited period
    for security.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Retention</h2>
  <table class="legal-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Data</th>
        <th>Retention</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Uploaded ZIP / downloaded repo content</td>
        <td>
          Processed in server memory only for the duration of your request. We do not intentionally
          persist raw archives or source files on disk or in a database after the request
          completes.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Generated documents in API response</td>
        <td>Returned to your browser; not stored on our servers by default.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Document history (localStorage)</td>
        <td>Stored on your device only, if you opt in.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Server logs (IP, User-Agent, etc.)</td>
        <td>
          Retained for up to 90 days unless a longer period is required for security investigations
          or legal compliance.
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    Ephemeral memory processing does not guarantee that all traces are instantly erased from every
    system layer (for example, log backups). We do not maintain a user content archive.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Security</h2>
  <p>
    We use HTTPS, access controls, upload size limits, zip-slip protections, rate limiting, and
    network isolation between public-facing and application layers. No method of transmission or
    storage is completely secure.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, restrict, or object
    to processing of personal data, and to data portability.
  </p>
  <p>
    Because we do not store submitted source code after processing, limiting further processing
    typically means not submitting new content and clearing document history in your browser
    (localStorage) if you enabled it. If applicable law grants you additional rights regarding data
    we may hold (such as server logs), you may exercise those rights through any contact channel we
    publish on <a href="https://reporili.tech">https://reporili.tech</a> when available.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Children</h2>
  <p>
    Reporili is not directed at children under 16 (or 13 where applicable). We do not knowingly
    collect children’s data.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Beta service</h2>
  <p>
    Reporili is in <strong>Beta</strong>. Features and data practices may change. We will update
    this policy when material changes occur.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may revise this Privacy Policy. The “Last updated” date will change. Continued use after
    changes constitutes acceptance where permitted by law.
  </p>
</LegalPage>
